-- Italy Beats Russia to Win Fed Cup Tennis Title for Fourth Time
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-11-03T13:41:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-03/italy-beats-russia-to-win-fed-cup-tennis-title-for-fourth-time.html
Italy clinched the Fed Cup tennis
title for the fourth time after building an unbeatable 3-0 lead
over Russia in the best-of-five final.  Sara Errani scored the crucial point with a 6-1, 6-1
victory over Alisa Kleybanova in Cagliari, Sardinia.  Yesterday, Roberta Vinci beat Alexandra Panova 5-7, 7-5, 8-6 and Errani defeated Irina Khromacheva 6-1, 6-4 in women’s
tennis’s top team competition.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 